-Drained Tired Cookies:
-Base Ingredients
132 g all-purpose flour
38 g dark brown sugar
213 g granulated sugar
9 tbsp unsalted butter
0.5 tsp kosher salt
0.5 tsp baking soda
50 g egg
-Flavor Ingredients
0.5 tsp clove
340 g chocolate
2.0 tsp vanilla
---
Instructions
Step 1: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F.
Step 2: Mix together dry ingredients, combining the following in a large bowl: flour, kosher salt, baking soda, clove. In another bowl, cream together the following: dark brown sugar, granulated sugar, unsalted butter, vanilla, egg.
Step 3: Gradually add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients, mixing well. Once mixed, add the chocolate.
Step 4: Let the mixture rest for 10 hours in the refrigerator. On a baking sheet lined with parchment paper, add 40 grams of dough, rolled into a sphere. Bake for  10 minutes, turning the sheet around halfway through the baking time.
Step 5: Let the cookies cool.